### 1) PROBING DOMAINS (Find Live Websites)

### Tool: `httpx`

### Purpose

Find **which subdomains have web services**.

### Command

```bash
httpx -l alive_subdomains.txt \
  -status-code \
  -title \
  -tech-detect \
  -o live_http.txt

```

### 2) WAYBACK URL COLLECTION

### Tool: `waybackurls` + `gau`

### Purpose

Find **old & hidden endpoints** (most bugs are here)

## waybackurls

```bash
cat live_http.txt | waybackurls > wayback.txt

```

## gau (better coverage)

```bash
cat live_http.txt | gau > gau.txt

```

## Combine & Clean

```bash
cat wayback.txt gau.txt |sort -u > all_urls.txt

```

## 4’ĖÅŌāŻ Incorrect input format

waybackurls [example.com](http://example.com/) > urls.txt   

Ō£ģ CORRECT:

```bash
waybackurls example.com

```

Same for gau:

```bash
gau example.com

```

### 3) JAVASCRIPT (JS) SCANNING

- `httpx`
- `LinkFinder`
- `SecretFinder`

## Extract JS URLs

```bash
grep "\.js" all_urls.txt |sort -u > js_files.txt

```

## Better JS filtering (recommended)

Avoid false positives like `.json`, `.jsp`:

```bash
grep -Ei "\.js($|\?)" all_urls.txt |sort -u > js_files.txt

```

## Optional: Check live JS files

```bash
httpx -l js_files.txt -status-code -mc 200 -o live_js.txt

```

